  <p>This policy explains what personal information I collect through <strong>damienbuilds.dev</strong>, why I collect it, and what your rights are under South Africa's <strong>Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA)</strong>. I've kept it in plain language, because a privacy policy you can't read isn't really protecting anyone.</p>

  <h2>Who's responsible for your information</h2>
  <p>The responsible party is <span class="insert">[ FULL LEGAL NAME ]</span>, trading as <strong>DamienBuilds</strong>, based in Phoenix, Durban, South Africa.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Information Officer:</strong> <span class="insert">[ FULL LEGAL NAME ]</span></li>
    <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:damien@damienbuilds.dev">damien@damienbuilds.dev</a></li>
    <li><strong>Address:</strong> <span class="insert">[ REGISTERED / POSTAL ADDRESS ]</span></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What I collect, and when</h2>
  <p>I only collect what you choose to give me. Specifically:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>When you use the contact form:</strong> your name, email address, optional phone/WhatsApp number, the service you're interested in, and whatever you type in your message.</li>
    <li><strong>When you join the launch list (pop-up):</strong> your name, email address, and an optional WhatsApp number.</li>
    <li><strong>Automatically:</strong> basic technical data (such as your IP address and browser type) is processed by my hosting provider to serve the site and keep it secure. I do not run advertising or analytics tracking on this site.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why I collect it</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To reply to your enquiry, prepare quotes, and deliver the work you've asked about.</li>
    <li>To let you know when DamienBuilds officially launches, if you joined the launch list.</li>
    <li>To keep basic records of who I've worked with and what was agreed.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>I rely on your <strong>consent</strong> (which you give by submitting a form) and on the need to take steps <strong>at your request before entering into a contract</strong>. I will never use your details for anything you didn't reasonably expect when you sent them.</p>

  <h2>Who I share it with</h2>
  <p>I don't sell your information, ever. A small number of trusted service providers (operators) process it on my behalf, purely to run the site and deliver messages to me:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Web3Forms</strong> — receives your form submission and emails it to me.</li>
    <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — hosts the website.</li>
    <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> — serves the site's fonts, which involves your browser contacting Google's servers.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Some of these providers are based outside South Africa, so your information may be processed in other countries. POPIA permits this where the provider is subject to comparable data-protection rules, which these providers are.</p>

  <h2>How long I keep it</h2>
  <p>I keep enquiry and client information only for as long as I reasonably need it — to respond to you, to deliver and support the work, and to meet any record-keeping obligations. If we don't end up working together, you can ask me to delete your details at any time.</p>

  <h2>Cookies and local storage</h2>
  <p>This site doesn't use advertising or tracking cookies. The launch pop-up uses a small piece of browser <strong>local storage</strong> to remember that you've already dismissed it, so it doesn't nag you on every visit. That's it.</p>

  <h2>How I protect it</h2>
  <p>I take reasonable technical and organisational steps to keep your information safe, including secure (HTTPS) connections and limiting who can access submissions. No system is perfectly secure, but I treat your details with the same care I'd want for my own.</p>

  <h2>Your rights under POPIA</h2>
  <p>You have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Ask what personal information I hold about you, and request a copy.</li>
    <li>Ask me to correct or delete information that's wrong or no longer needed.</li>
    <li>Object to how I'm using your information.</li>
    <li>Withdraw your consent at any time.</li>
    <li>Complain to the Information Regulator if you believe I've mishandled your information.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To exercise any of these, just email <a href="mailto:damien@damienbuilds.dev">damien@damienbuilds.dev</a> and I'll sort it out.</p>

  <h2>The Information Regulator</h2>
  <p>If you're not happy with how I've handled your information, you can contact the regulator directly:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>The Information Regulator (South Africa)</strong></li>
    <li>Email: <a href="mailto:enquiries@inforegulator.org.za">enquiries@inforegulator.org.za</a> / complaints: <a href="mailto:POPIAComplaints@inforegulator.org.za">POPIAComplaints@inforegulator.org.za</a></li>
    <li>Website: <a href="https://inforegulator.org.za" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">inforegulator.org.za</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>If I change how I handle your information, I'll update this page and the "last updated" date above. For anything you're unsure about, email me — I'd rather over-explain than leave you guessing.</p>
